SIMPLE: giving
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Giving
<hw>Giv"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
bestowing as a gift; a conferring or imparting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gift; a benefaction.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of softening, breaking, or yielding.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Upon the first <xex>giving</xex> of the weather.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Giving in</b></col>, <cd>a falling inwards; a
collapse.</cd> -- <col><b>Giving out</b></col>, <cd>anything uttered or
asserted; an outgiving.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>givings out</qex> were of an infinite distance⟦br⟧
From his true meant design.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gizzard</ent>⟦br⟧
